<h1><a href="index.html">Replicators</a>: B0235/S0</h1>

<p><a href="http://fano.ics.uci.edu/ca/rules/b0235s0/">B0235/S0</a>
has a diagonal replicator that repeats with period 4, moving
diagonally at speed c/2.</p>

<p align="CENTER"><a href="b0235s0.lif"><img src="b0235s0.gif"
width="23" height="23" alt="B0235/S0 2c/4 diagonal replicator"></a></p>

<p>The same rule also has a small 7c/14 orthogonal replicator:</p>

<p align="CENTER"><a href="b0235s0-or.lif"><img src=
"b0235s0-or.gif" width="11" height="15" alt="B0235/S0 7c/14 orthogonal replicator"></a></p>

<p>The orthogonal replicator can pull a dot behind it at 14c/28,
making the largest known spaceship with only three live cells in any rule:</p>

<p align="CENTER"><a href="b0235s0-ss.lif"><img src=
"b0235s0-ss.gif" width="35" height="15" alt="B0235/S0 14c/28 spaceship"></a></p>

